gomodel:SYNGO_5007  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2-3: IgSF21 is a postsynaptic protein that interacts specifically with neurexin2α (gene NRXN2) and not any of the other neurexin isoforms.\n\nFigure 7: IgSF21 knockout reduces (but does not abolish) synaptic transmission.\n\nAuthors propose that IgSF21 modulates synaptic transmission through trans-synaptic signaling via neurexin2α.. Experimental description: Result section, Figure 7 legend: \"Inhibitory synaptic transmission is reduced in Igsf21 -/- mice\"\n\nM&M: \" Igsf21 -/- mice were bred into the C57BL/6 background. Genotyping of Igsf21 -/-mice was performed using the following two primers: P1 (5'-TCA GAC AAT GGT CCC TAT GAG-3') and P2 (5'-CTC ATG GCA CTT GCT CCT TG-3').\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5007" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

